											<section class="main bio authorbio">
							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/trina-moyles/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Trina Moyles is a Yukon-based environmental journalist and the author of several nonfiction books, including <em>Women Who Dig</em> (University of Regina Press, 2018), <em>Lookout </em>(Random House, 2021), and the forthcoming <em>Black Bear</em> (Knopf, 2025). Her writing has been widely published in <em>Canadian Geographic, </em>the<em> Globe and Mail</em>, <em>The Narwhal, </em>and other publications. She has an MFA in creative writing from the University of British Columbia. Moyles lives in Whitehorse with her two huskies.</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="520" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/trina-moyles-1-520x520.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="Trina Moyles" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/trina-moyles-1-520x520.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/trina-moyles-1-150x150.jpg 150w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/trina-moyles-1-768x768.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/trina-moyles-1-900x900.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/trina-moyles-1.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
											</div>
											</a>
																																																																	<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/micheal-code/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Michael Code is a cinematographer and member of the Sayisi Dene First Nation, with over a decade of filmmaking experience in Northern Canada and beyond. Recently, he has worked on feature films including <em>River of Life</em>, as well as series like <em>The Nature of Things</em>, <em>Arctic Secrets</em>, <em>The Amazing Race Canada</em>, and <em>Gold Rush</em>. He is currently co-producing a feature documentary about polar bears.</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="520" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/michael-code-520x520.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="Michael Code" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/michael-code-520x520.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/michael-code-150x150.jpg 150w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/michael-code-768x768.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/michael-code-900x900.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/michael-code.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
											</div>
											</a>
